1
00:00:05,801 --> 00:00:07,501
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,571 --> 00:00:09,171
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,871 --> 00:00:11,941
(Episode 37)

4
00:00:12,011 --> 00:00:13,881
What? Why?

5
00:00:14,281 --> 00:00:17,481
To be honest, we're also considering
the possibility of foul play.

6
00:00:18,751 --> 00:00:22,021
- Foul play?
- Yes. For example,

7
00:00:22,791 --> 00:00:24,151
a kidnapping, for instance.

8
00:00:26,991 --> 00:00:31,491
On that note, did he make
any enemies about 30 years ago?

9
00:00:32,501 --> 00:00:33,861
Enemies?

10
00:00:34,931 --> 00:00:37,071
No, who on earth would...

11
00:00:50,511 --> 00:00:53,021
Hey. I'm heading out for a bit.

12
00:01:14,601 --> 00:01:15,971
<i>Makes my heart pound</i>

13
00:01:15,971 --> 00:01:17,141
<i>It pounds</i>

14
00:01:18,881 --> 00:01:20,811
Thump thump?

15
00:01:21,911 --> 00:01:23,181
<i>You are my personal IV drip</i>

16
00:01:23,181 --> 00:01:24,751
<i>My very own intravenous shot</i>

17
00:01:25,411 --> 00:01:28,221
<i>You're the cure for my arrhythmia</i>

18
00:01:35,691 --> 00:01:36,691
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

19
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:38,931
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

20
00:01:46,341 --> 00:01:47,371
(Missing Person)

21
00:01:47,441 --> 00:01:48,501
(From Onjeong Market's
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,)

22
00:01:48,571 --> 00:01:49,641
(we are looking for
Dr. Gong Gi Cheol.)

23
00:01:50,041 --> 00:01:51,371
Jeong Han, what's wrong?

24
00:01:52,311 --> 00:01:54,711
What did the police say? Why?

25
00:01:55,481 --> 00:01:57,111
It's about Father.

26
00:01:57,951 --> 00:01:59,081
What about him?

27
00:01:59,721 --> 00:02:00,721
Father...

28
00:02:01,351 --> 00:02:03,051
might be caught up in a crime...

29
00:02:03,951 --> 00:02:04,951
I mean...

30
00:02:05,421 --> 00:02:08,021
they're saying
he could've been kidnapped.

31
00:02:08,321 --> 00:02:10,591
- What?
- They asked me...

32
00:02:11,161 --> 00:02:14,161
if he had any enemies.

33
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:18,841
So someone might have done this
to Father on purpose?

34
00:02:19,641 --> 00:02:21,871
Now, try not to be too alarmed.

35
00:02:22,741 --> 00:02:26,081
Let's just keep an open mind
about all the possibilities.

36
00:02:27,081 --> 00:02:28,911
No, that's impossible.

37
00:02:30,151 --> 00:02:31,451
As far as I know,

38
00:02:31,811 --> 00:02:34,381
he never did anything
to harm anyone.

39
00:02:34,721 --> 00:02:38,861
I agree, but you never know.
So let's all think hard, okay?

40
00:03:07,581 --> 00:03:11,651
My darling love, once so kind

41
00:03:11,891 --> 00:03:13,961
Have you forgotten me?

42
00:03:15,391 --> 00:03:19,731
Have you already forgotten me?

43
00:03:27,601 --> 00:03:29,171
Do I play the guitar?

44
00:03:30,871 --> 00:03:32,411
(Missing Person)

45
00:03:32,481 --> 00:03:35,141
If you happen to see him,
please give me a call.

46
00:03:36,251 --> 00:03:37,951
- Take care.
- Thanks.

47
00:03:40,151 --> 00:03:44,091
Perfect timing.
I was just about to call you.

48
00:03:45,191 --> 00:03:48,991
I heard it was a misunderstanding
with the woman from the clinic.

49
00:03:49,591 --> 00:03:54,261
Yes. So we're trying to start
a proper search now.

50
00:03:54,961 --> 00:03:56,031
So...

51
00:03:56,301 --> 00:04:00,971
when you saw Dr. Gong's double
in Seongdam,

52
00:04:01,341 --> 00:04:03,741
did you notice anything strange?

53
00:04:03,971 --> 00:04:07,111
I don't know.
I only saw him for a second.

54
00:04:07,581 --> 00:04:10,011
Was he with anyone?

55
00:04:10,081 --> 00:04:14,551
A woman was with him, so I assumed
it was the one from the clinic.

56
00:04:15,281 --> 00:04:17,291
- A woman?
- Yes, a woman.

57
00:04:26,131 --> 00:04:27,661
Did you finish the work
you got yesterday?

58
00:04:28,461 --> 00:04:29,631
No, not yet.

59
00:04:30,331 --> 00:04:31,831
What's taking you so long?

60
00:04:32,131 --> 00:04:33,441
All right.

61
00:04:40,281 --> 00:04:41,281
Oh my.

62
00:04:44,051 --> 00:04:45,151
What is this?

63
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:48,281
I found it while taking out
the trash, so I picked it up.

64
00:04:48,421 --> 00:04:50,251
I told you never to go outside!

65
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,191
What were you thinking?
What if the police caught you?

66
00:04:53,961 --> 00:04:56,591
Why bring this filthy thing in here?

67
00:04:57,061 --> 00:04:59,301
- Honestly.
- Enough. Give it to me.

68
00:04:59,401 --> 00:05:00,901
It's time. Just take your medicine.

69
00:05:02,001 --> 00:05:04,501
Even when I'm gone, take your meds
when the alarm goes off.

70
00:05:05,901 --> 00:05:09,241
You know you could die
if you don't. Got it?

71
00:05:13,241 --> 00:05:14,241
Gosh.

72
00:05:19,351 --> 00:05:21,351
(Oral Medication)

73
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:25,491
(Handover to Gong Ju Ah)

74
00:05:25,551 --> 00:05:26,961
(Collection references,
full collection lineup)

75
00:05:27,261 --> 00:05:29,891
I uploaded the collection materials,

76
00:05:29,891 --> 00:05:31,761
and as for event feedback
and references,

77
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:33,101
I've organized them by season.

78
00:05:33,501 --> 00:05:34,561
Got it.

79
00:05:36,871 --> 00:05:39,241
I heard the director had
Managing Director Hong forced out.

80
00:05:40,471 --> 00:05:43,971
And one more thing.
The stalled Paris Claramont deal.

81
00:05:44,041 --> 00:05:45,671
Director Yang saved it!

82
00:05:45,981 --> 00:05:46,981
- Incredible!
- Yes!

83
00:05:48,581 --> 00:05:51,111
He's finally gone! Finally!

84
00:05:56,591 --> 00:05:58,491
All right, is everyone here?

85
00:06:00,091 --> 00:06:03,661
First, I'd like to apologize
for any confusion about my position.

86
00:06:04,261 --> 00:06:06,131
My resignation has been rescinded...

87
00:06:06,561 --> 00:06:09,731
and the order is back on track,
so let's hit the ground running.

88
00:06:09,801 --> 00:06:10,801
- Yes.
- Yes.

89
00:06:11,471 --> 00:06:14,401
Okay, let's begin
the styling class meeting.

90
00:06:16,071 --> 00:06:17,241
Here's the concept proposal.

91
00:06:18,141 --> 00:06:20,511
The VIP clients we invited
to the One-Point Lesson...

92
00:06:20,581 --> 00:06:22,411
The plan is to invite them back.

93
00:06:22,781 --> 00:06:26,051
- Okay. Who's running the event?
- I am.

94
00:06:26,121 --> 00:06:28,081
Who did you choose as the client
for the live styling session?

95
00:06:28,251 --> 00:06:31,491
We've decided on Cha Se Ri.
Your mother.

96
00:06:32,021 --> 00:06:34,291
Given the unfortunate incident
at the last event,

97
00:06:34,621 --> 00:06:37,491
I want to make it up to her
in front of the other VIPs.

98
00:06:39,361 --> 00:06:41,131
I see. I'll get in touch with her.

99
00:06:41,201 --> 00:06:44,031
It would be good for you to finish
on a high note before you leave.

100
00:06:44,571 --> 00:06:45,571
Understood.

101
00:06:46,301 --> 00:06:50,411
This is an important event,
so please prepare meticulously.

102
00:06:50,741 --> 00:06:54,041
The event host and I
will be wearing company attire,

103
00:06:54,111 --> 00:06:56,811
so I expect you
to dress accordingly. That is all.

104
00:07:07,791 --> 00:07:10,791
They both looked ready for a fight.

105
00:07:13,461 --> 00:07:15,601
It's a huge shame
that Ms. Gong is leaving,

106
00:07:15,971 --> 00:07:19,741
but it's a relief for the division
that at least Pacu Nacho is staying.

107
00:07:20,471 --> 00:07:24,241
We got Claramont's advance,
so our division can finally breathe.

108
00:07:25,411 --> 00:07:28,581
He's so good at his job.
Too bad he's hopeless with love.

109
00:07:28,641 --> 00:07:29,781
Tell me about it.

110
00:07:30,251 --> 00:07:32,781
He says to sign the long-term deal
as promised.

111
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:36,321
So, is he finally settling down
at Taehan for good?

112
00:07:37,251 --> 00:07:39,261
Does relying on him so much
make me look incompetent?

113
00:07:39,791 --> 00:07:43,861
Incompetent? Keeping a gifted person
is a talent in itself.

114
00:07:44,791 --> 00:07:45,931
I like that answer.

115
00:07:47,261 --> 00:07:50,701
By the way, you know Director Baek
is completely losing it right now?

116
00:07:50,831 --> 00:07:52,001
He's just seething.

117
00:07:53,541 --> 00:07:55,541
(Taehan Group)

118
00:08:00,611 --> 00:08:02,281
Okay, perfect!

119
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:12,051
Director Yang?

120
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:14,891
Yes. He came to see me
after the funeral,

121
00:08:15,691 --> 00:08:19,031
and asked me to tell you
he probably can't quit after all.

122
00:08:19,161 --> 00:08:23,331
Why did he have to report that?

123
00:08:23,401 --> 00:08:27,241
- That kid is something else.
- He regrets breaking his promise.

124
00:08:28,241 --> 00:08:30,841
He made the right call.
With so much going on in the family,

125
00:08:31,011 --> 00:08:32,681
of course he has to stay in Korea.

126
00:08:33,041 --> 00:08:36,051
Besides, Ju Ah is quitting anyway.

127
00:08:37,911 --> 00:08:38,951
She is quitting, right?

128
00:08:40,221 --> 00:08:42,621
Of course. Mother...

129
00:08:43,051 --> 00:08:46,021
It's about Dae Han.

130
00:08:46,391 --> 00:08:47,691
- I'm home.
- Well...

131
00:08:47,991 --> 00:08:49,631
- Welcome home.
- Yes.

132
00:08:49,991 --> 00:08:53,201
I thought the "Human Theater"
wrap party was tonight.

133
00:08:53,261 --> 00:08:54,431
Why didn't you go?

134
00:08:55,031 --> 00:08:57,101
I have to look after you.

135
00:08:58,571 --> 00:09:01,501
I'll go change and be right out,
so get ready to do some stretches.

136
00:09:01,841 --> 00:09:03,071
Good. Glad you're home.

137
00:09:05,811 --> 00:09:07,481
What about Dae Han?

138
00:09:08,981 --> 00:09:10,181
It's nothing.

139
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,051
Father.

140
00:09:19,491 --> 00:09:22,421
I have the "Human Theater"
wrap party tonight.

141
00:09:22,861 --> 00:09:24,131
You go on home ahead of me.

142
00:09:24,431 --> 00:09:28,501
- Any news on finding Gi Cheol?
- The police are helping us.

143
00:09:29,101 --> 00:09:33,841
This weekend, we'll put up banners
and hand out more flyers nearby.

144
00:09:34,801 --> 00:09:37,111
I'll cover whatever it costs,

145
00:09:38,071 --> 00:09:40,211
so do whatever it takes
to help them.

146
00:09:40,281 --> 00:09:44,581
Yes. Father, be sure to eat dinner
when you get home.

147
00:09:44,911 --> 00:09:45,921
I will.

148
00:09:46,951 --> 00:09:48,681
Not until we find Gi Cheol,

149
00:09:49,221 --> 00:09:51,791
I'm going to stay alive
no matter what.

150
00:09:52,151 --> 00:09:54,261
Please don't talk like that.

151
00:09:54,691 --> 00:09:57,161
What would I do
if I lost you too, Father?

152
00:09:59,761 --> 00:10:03,231
- Great work.
- Great work.

153
00:10:06,871 --> 00:10:08,941
Wow, we're really done now.

154
00:10:09,411 --> 00:10:13,181
- Thank you all for your hard work.
- Oh, please. You did all the work.

155
00:10:13,241 --> 00:10:18,011
- You did all the hard work. Really.
- In fact, thanks to you,

156
00:10:18,481 --> 00:10:22,221
my mother got to see the whole show
before she passed away.

157
00:10:22,551 --> 00:10:24,121
I'm truly grateful for that.

158
00:10:24,451 --> 00:10:27,361
I'm so sorry
we couldn't make it to the funeral.

159
00:10:27,421 --> 00:10:31,731
The crew and I pitched in
a little something.

160
00:10:31,791 --> 00:10:35,101
Oh, no, you shouldn't have.
The thought is more than enough.

161
00:10:35,501 --> 00:10:37,171
- Oh, I can't...
- Please, take it.

162
00:10:38,901 --> 00:10:42,301
And Dr. Gong,
I really hope you find your father.

163
00:10:42,401 --> 00:10:44,911
Yes. Thank you. I appreciate it.

164
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:48,441
- If you'll excuse us...
- Oh, yes, of course.

165
00:10:49,781 --> 00:10:51,111
Goodness...

166
00:10:51,411 --> 00:10:55,481
Hey, come on, just take it. Okay?
Think of it as a gift from your mom.

167
00:10:55,721 --> 00:10:57,691
All right. I'll gratefully accept.

168
00:10:59,991 --> 00:11:02,091
Hey, about this place...

169
00:11:02,491 --> 00:11:03,931
What, are you ordering more?

170
00:11:04,061 --> 00:11:07,831
No, I was just looking for something
to get for Seong Mi to-go,

171
00:11:07,901 --> 00:11:10,131
but there's nothing suitable.

172
00:11:10,671 --> 00:11:13,101
You're good to Seong Mi lately.

173
00:11:13,601 --> 00:11:15,771
Not even drinking
on a day like this.

174
00:11:15,941 --> 00:11:18,741
Of course.
Imagine if your wife were sick.

175
00:11:18,811 --> 00:11:22,381
- Feels like the world's collapsing.
- I bet...

176
00:11:23,311 --> 00:11:24,951
You should've treated her better
before she got sick.

177
00:11:25,611 --> 00:11:29,551
Gosh. You married my first love
only to make her suffer.

178
00:11:29,721 --> 00:11:32,861
What, are you drunk already?
You've barely had anything to drink.

179
00:11:33,191 --> 00:11:36,061
Quiet. They'll think you're serious.

180
00:11:36,461 --> 00:11:38,331
Jeong Han, honestly...

181
00:11:39,291 --> 00:11:40,301
It's true, isn't it?

182
00:11:40,861 --> 00:11:44,401
Oh, it's true? Want a beating?
Want to go at it again?

183
00:11:45,131 --> 00:11:49,571
- Whatever. Just eat.
- Right. You should eat too.

184
00:11:50,371 --> 00:11:53,111
- Enjoy your meal!
- Thanks. Great working with you.

185
00:11:53,181 --> 00:11:54,511
- Great working with you.
- You too.

186
00:11:55,581 --> 00:11:58,611
- Excuse me. How much are these?
- They're ten dollars.

187
00:11:58,681 --> 00:12:02,021
- Oh, I'll take two, please.
- Okay, one moment.

188
00:12:02,081 --> 00:12:03,891
Wait, what are you doing?

189
00:12:03,951 --> 00:12:08,361
It's on me.
I owe Seong Mi a lot too.

190
00:12:09,191 --> 00:12:12,661
Oh, you mean that session
you had with her?

191
00:12:13,101 --> 00:12:15,401
What? Oh, you heard about that.

192
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:17,331
I really am grateful.

193
00:12:18,401 --> 00:12:20,901
No, man. I should be thanking you.
You know?

194
00:12:20,971 --> 00:12:24,471
- Counseling helps Seong Mi, too.
- Oh, really?

195
00:12:24,541 --> 00:12:28,911
- Yes, see her more often. Okay?
- Yes, I think I will.

196
00:12:29,451 --> 00:12:30,451
Here you go.

197
00:12:30,511 --> 00:12:32,311
- Oh, thank you so much.
- I don't need the receipt.

198
00:12:32,381 --> 00:12:33,421
- Okay.
- Yes, thanks.

199
00:12:33,481 --> 00:12:35,681
- Thanks again. Have a good night.
- Take care.

200
00:12:35,751 --> 00:12:37,551
- Thanks, man.
- Of course. Hope it's good.

201
00:12:43,731 --> 00:12:46,501
Thank goodness. I heard you two were
on a trial separation.

202
00:12:46,761 --> 00:12:47,761
Trial separation?

203
00:12:49,871 --> 00:12:53,741
Hey, but seriously,
why'd you see Seong Mi for help?

204
00:12:53,941 --> 00:12:55,341
Is something wrong?

205
00:12:56,211 --> 00:12:58,041
Well, I...

206
00:12:59,141 --> 00:13:00,741
My daughter...

207
00:13:01,011 --> 00:13:03,751
Gosh, did you get drunk
without even drinking?

208
00:13:03,811 --> 00:13:07,251
- You already have a daughter...
- Another one.

209
00:13:07,721 --> 00:13:09,491
The daughter Se Ri had.

210
00:13:11,451 --> 00:13:12,451
What?

211
00:13:12,891 --> 00:13:14,561
It turns out, a long time ago,

212
00:13:15,221 --> 00:13:17,791
my wife had a daughter
she gave up for adoption.

213
00:13:19,231 --> 00:13:22,031
Oh, she did?

214
00:13:22,431 --> 00:13:24,531
Yes. Apparently so.

215
00:13:25,201 --> 00:13:26,741
She knew how much I used to...

216
00:13:27,241 --> 00:13:30,071
despise women
who abandoned their children.

217
00:13:30,641 --> 00:13:35,081
- So she hid it from me.
- Oh, right. Of course she would.

218
00:13:35,741 --> 00:13:39,681
Hey, did you guys
fight a lot about it?

219
00:13:39,821 --> 00:13:40,951
Hardly a fight.

220
00:13:41,981 --> 00:13:43,891
I was the one who acted like a jerk.

221
00:13:44,451 --> 00:13:47,361
I'm pretty surprised too,

222
00:13:47,961 --> 00:13:51,491
but she's your wife
who raised your son, after all.

223
00:13:52,061 --> 00:13:54,061
So are you taking her back?

224
00:13:54,431 --> 00:13:56,631
Yes, I'm going to.

225
00:13:57,331 --> 00:13:59,841
Jeong Han, listen...

226
00:14:00,901 --> 00:14:02,171
About Dae Han...

227
00:14:02,641 --> 00:14:05,541
Do you think he'd accept
Dong Suk's son, Ji Hu?

228
00:14:07,781 --> 00:14:11,111
If your family is on board,

229
00:14:11,611 --> 00:14:15,081
we'd like to give them our blessing
to be together.

230
00:14:22,491 --> 00:14:25,031
Here, honey. This is the best part.

231
00:14:25,291 --> 00:14:29,101
- Here you go. Open wide.
- Okay.

232
00:14:29,871 --> 00:14:34,471
It's so rich. This is delicious.
You should've stayed to catch up.

233
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,341
Why'd you come home so early?

234
00:14:36,411 --> 00:14:40,281
Because this is your favorite.
I wanted you to have it right away.

235
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:44,181
It's so nice to see you two
being so lovey-dovey lately.

236
00:14:44,451 --> 00:14:47,921
Isn't it?
It's lovely to see you two caring.

237
00:14:50,951 --> 00:14:54,421
Mom, about Dae Han...

238
00:14:55,161 --> 00:14:58,331
Won't you please give him
and Dong Suk your blessing?

239
00:14:58,991 --> 00:15:00,001
Hey, Jeong Han.

240
00:15:00,861 --> 00:15:02,901
Why are you bringing this up now?

241
00:15:02,901 --> 00:15:04,501
We should be
focused on finding Father.

242
00:15:04,571 --> 00:15:07,101
And who knows
how long that's going to take?

243
00:15:09,611 --> 00:15:12,041
- I'm home!
- There she is. Welcome home, Ju Ah.

244
00:15:12,111 --> 00:15:16,181
- Ju Ah, you're home.
- What's with the late-night snack?

245
00:15:16,451 --> 00:15:18,281
And after I went to the trouble
of buying something yummy.

246
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:22,051
- What is it?
- It's the popular dessert.

247
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:25,121
I thought something sweet
might cheer everyone up.

248
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:29,761
Gosh, thanks. I already feel better,
and I haven't even had any.

249
00:15:30,161 --> 00:15:31,361
Come sit over here, Ju Ah.

250
00:15:31,661 --> 00:15:33,361
Let me put the cake
in the fridge real quick.

251
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:38,031
Mom, back to what we were discussing
with Dae Han. Well?

252
00:15:38,601 --> 00:15:43,171
The Korean medicine clinic family
must be grieving after the funeral.

253
00:15:43,241 --> 00:15:45,671
I just feel like it's too soon
to bring it up.

254
00:15:46,411 --> 00:15:50,181
The elder already summoned them
to the house.

255
00:15:50,251 --> 00:15:54,081
Seong Mi, that was only because
Dong Suk was struggling so much.

256
00:15:54,151 --> 00:15:57,491
No, that's not it.
Bucket brought it up first.

257
00:15:57,551 --> 00:16:01,921
He said he wants to make it official
and asked for our family's opinion.

258
00:16:01,991 --> 00:16:05,731
- Really?
- Bucket really said that?

259
00:16:05,791 --> 00:16:07,301
I'm telling you, he did.

260
00:16:07,601 --> 00:16:11,671
Dae Han, if you don't believe me,
go ask him yourself tomorrow.

261
00:16:16,271 --> 00:16:18,041
You don't seem very keen
on the idea.

262
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:20,041
What's wrong, Mother?

263
00:16:21,581 --> 00:16:23,851
It's because of Ju Ah.

264
00:16:24,511 --> 00:16:25,581
Ju Ah?

265
00:16:26,551 --> 00:16:29,081
If I give Dae Han my blessing,

266
00:16:29,351 --> 00:16:31,621
don't you think Ju Ah will be upset?

267
00:16:32,091 --> 00:16:35,261
It's not like our disapproval is
why they broke up.

268
00:16:35,361 --> 00:16:36,391
Even so...

269
00:16:37,061 --> 00:16:39,361
It still played a part in it.

270
00:16:39,931 --> 00:16:40,931
What about you?

271
00:16:41,331 --> 00:16:42,331
Me?

272
00:16:42,731 --> 00:16:47,141
If it works out, we'll be in-laws
with that family.

273
00:16:48,001 --> 00:16:52,271
It's not like I'll have to deal
with them directly, right?

274
00:16:59,111 --> 00:17:02,821
- Looking for something specific?
- Yes.

275
00:17:03,251 --> 00:17:07,621
I work out a lot,
so my knees, shoulders, and arms...

276
00:17:07,691 --> 00:17:09,791
get pretty stiff and sore.

277
00:17:09,861 --> 00:17:13,361
Then, that product over there
might be good for you.

278
00:17:13,431 --> 00:17:15,931
- Would you like to give it a try?
- Should I?

279
00:17:18,671 --> 00:17:19,701
Right this way...

280
00:17:22,171 --> 00:17:24,941
And I'd also like something
that's easy to carry around...

281
00:17:25,011 --> 00:17:28,381
- and use on the go.
- I see.

282
00:17:29,311 --> 00:17:31,811
In that case,
would you like to try this?

283
00:17:32,181 --> 00:17:35,251
It's great for applying lightly
when you're sore after a workout.

284
00:17:35,451 --> 00:17:39,491
For this one,
you just apply it like this.

285
00:17:47,261 --> 00:17:49,971
Wow, that feels really refreshing.
I like it.

286
00:17:50,631 --> 00:17:53,171
I'll take a few of these
to share with my family.

287
00:17:53,171 --> 00:17:54,171
- Of course.
- Thanks.

288
00:17:54,171 --> 00:17:55,301
I'll wrap them up nicely for you.

289
00:17:56,371 --> 00:17:57,371
What?

290
00:17:58,211 --> 00:18:00,941
- Hello.
- Hey, Min Seo.

291
00:18:01,311 --> 00:18:02,311
Son!

292
00:18:03,411 --> 00:18:05,151
(3H Acupressure Bed)

293
00:18:05,651 --> 00:18:07,681
A styling class?

294
00:18:08,321 --> 00:18:12,551
- You want me to get on stage?
- You're just doing a demonstration.

295
00:18:12,791 --> 00:18:16,491
During the One-Point Lesson,

296
00:18:16,561 --> 00:18:18,731
I fell right in front of the VIPs.

297
00:18:19,291 --> 00:18:21,601
I admit I want
to look good this time.

298
00:18:21,701 --> 00:18:25,831
Right.
So Ms. Gong will be your stylist.

299
00:18:26,401 --> 00:18:28,201
Yes, that's not a bad idea.

300
00:18:28,571 --> 00:18:32,311
You'll need a fitting beforehand,
so I'll be in touch.

301
00:18:32,941 --> 00:18:33,941
Got it.

302
00:18:34,681 --> 00:18:38,851
By the way, did you hear about
my aunt and the manager?

303
00:18:39,311 --> 00:18:41,621
You mean how he got kicked out
when he came to the house?

304
00:18:41,681 --> 00:18:43,051
No, I mean what happened after that.

305
00:18:43,051 --> 00:18:44,891
Father and grandfather summoned him,

306
00:18:45,051 --> 00:18:48,921
- so he came to our house.
- He did?

307
00:18:49,191 --> 00:18:52,661
Yes. I think they did it because
my aunt is struggling so much.

308
00:18:53,401 --> 00:18:57,001
Don't tell me they're going
to give them their blessing.

309
00:18:57,131 --> 00:18:58,501
Shouldn't they?

310
00:18:59,031 --> 00:19:01,601
After all, the reason they couldn't
be together is gone.

311
00:19:03,211 --> 00:19:05,941
I suppose that's true.

312
00:19:07,041 --> 00:19:08,941
Well, I'm not so sure.

313
00:19:09,541 --> 00:19:12,481
I know you're preoccupied
with finding Gi Cheol,

314
00:19:13,581 --> 00:19:17,621
but Dong Suk and Dae Han
aren't getting any younger,

315
00:19:18,221 --> 00:19:21,961
so I was thinking we should let them
get married before it's too late.

316
00:19:23,591 --> 00:19:28,361
But it's only been a few days
since In Ok passed away.

317
00:19:29,231 --> 00:19:30,701
Are you sure you're okay with this?

318
00:19:31,731 --> 00:19:34,801
I just want something happy
to happen as soon as possible.

319
00:19:35,571 --> 00:19:36,571
That...

320
00:19:37,311 --> 00:19:40,411
it's what my wife would have wanted.

321
00:19:45,381 --> 00:19:46,381
What?

322
00:19:46,921 --> 00:19:48,081
Mom, wait. I...

323
00:19:48,751 --> 00:19:50,691
We really don't have to
rush into anything.

324
00:19:51,021 --> 00:19:53,121
No, let's.

325
00:19:53,791 --> 00:19:56,491
All the years you've lost,
it's such a waste.

326
00:19:56,891 --> 00:19:58,531
If it weren't for what happened,

327
00:19:58,791 --> 00:20:02,231
you two could have been
together long ago.

328
00:20:03,801 --> 00:20:04,801
You think so?

329
00:20:05,471 --> 00:20:07,001
After all this time,

330
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:10,411
for you two to find your way
back to each other,

331
00:20:10,941 --> 00:20:12,341
she must be the one for you.

332
00:20:13,111 --> 00:20:17,211
I know, but I'm not sure it's right,
with everything that's going on.

333
00:20:17,781 --> 00:20:21,281
If you give us your blessing,
we'll quietly support each other.

334
00:20:22,751 --> 00:20:24,091
What if...

335
00:20:26,221 --> 00:20:28,691
your father comes back?

336
00:20:29,961 --> 00:20:34,431
I think he'd be so happy
to see you two together.

337
00:20:36,131 --> 00:20:37,131
Yes.

338
00:20:37,831 --> 00:20:41,041
When I think about Dong Suk,

339
00:20:41,601 --> 00:20:45,141
my heart just breaks for her.

340
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:47,111
So, Gong Dae Han.

341
00:20:48,981 --> 00:20:49,981
You treat her right.

342
00:20:50,881 --> 00:20:51,881
Understand?

343
00:20:53,621 --> 00:20:54,621
Yes.

344
00:20:55,751 --> 00:20:56,751
You're right, Mom.

345
00:20:59,961 --> 00:21:02,961
Grandfather, what's going on?
Why did you call us all here?

346
00:21:04,161 --> 00:21:06,961
Dong Ik, Dong Suk...

347
00:21:08,431 --> 00:21:09,431
I...

348
00:21:11,231 --> 00:21:12,331
I'm sorry.

349
00:21:13,441 --> 00:21:14,541
Because of me...

350
00:21:16,601 --> 00:21:19,771
you lived for 30 years
without your mother.

351
00:21:24,351 --> 00:21:27,781
I knew the only place she could go
was her parents' home.

352
00:21:27,951 --> 00:21:32,021
You reminded me so much
of your mother...

353
00:21:32,951 --> 00:21:35,191
that it was devastating
just to look at you.

354
00:21:37,431 --> 00:21:38,791
So I was cold to you.

355
00:21:39,761 --> 00:21:41,161
No, Father.

356
00:21:42,131 --> 00:21:44,201
Father, you were always good to me.

357
00:21:46,071 --> 00:21:48,371
I'm sorry for
blaming everything on you.

358
00:21:52,541 --> 00:21:53,541
Ji Hu.

359
00:21:54,211 --> 00:21:57,451
Do you like him? Dae Han?

360
00:21:57,851 --> 00:21:58,881
Pardon?

361
00:21:59,481 --> 00:22:00,621
Yes, of course.

362
00:22:01,921 --> 00:22:04,151
Grandfather,
what are you getting at?

363
00:22:04,591 --> 00:22:07,691
Dong Suk, before it gets any warmer,

364
00:22:08,591 --> 00:22:09,591
you and Dae Han...

365
00:22:10,861 --> 00:22:11,861
are to be married.

366
00:22:12,931 --> 00:22:13,931
Oh my!

367
00:22:14,231 --> 00:22:15,801
Grandfather,
do you really mean that?

368
00:22:16,131 --> 00:22:19,271
I've arranged for our families
to have dinner together soon.

369
00:22:19,731 --> 00:22:22,801
That's wonderful.
Congratulations, Aunt.

370
00:22:40,591 --> 00:22:41,591
Dong Suk.

371
00:22:43,461 --> 00:22:44,591
Have you eaten anything?

372
00:22:46,031 --> 00:22:47,961
I must look like a mess, right?

373
00:22:49,661 --> 00:22:52,231
What?
No, you look even more beautiful.

374
00:23:01,211 --> 00:23:02,541
Did you hear what the elders said?

375
00:23:03,081 --> 00:23:05,151
Should we really be doing this?

376
00:23:05,781 --> 00:23:08,881
We haven't even found
your father yet.

377
00:23:09,151 --> 00:23:10,151
We'll find him.

378
00:23:11,051 --> 00:23:12,451
We'll find him, no matter what.

379
00:23:13,191 --> 00:23:15,091
And we'll show him
how happy we're going to be.

380
00:23:20,761 --> 00:23:21,761
Ji Hu...

381
00:23:23,231 --> 00:23:26,001
said he wanted to be my son
in his next life,

382
00:23:27,341 --> 00:23:29,401
now he'll be my son in this life.

383
00:23:30,571 --> 00:23:32,371
And we can tackle
our bucket list together.

384
00:23:35,741 --> 00:23:39,951
You're too good for me.

385
00:23:41,081 --> 00:23:42,681
Don't say things like that.
It scares me.

386
00:23:43,451 --> 00:23:44,451
But...

387
00:23:45,951 --> 00:23:47,161
I'll accept it.

388
00:23:49,691 --> 00:23:52,461
I'll believe my mom sent you
to me...

389
00:23:53,161 --> 00:23:55,901
as a gift
so I wouldn't be lonely anymore.

390
00:23:59,031 --> 00:24:01,101
And I will accept this gift.

391
00:24:03,741 --> 00:24:04,741
Okay.

392
00:24:06,141 --> 00:24:07,311
Let's get all our crying done today.

393
00:24:07,881 --> 00:24:08,941
We'll cry it all out today...

394
00:24:10,481 --> 00:24:11,511
and from now on, we'll smile.

395
00:24:12,851 --> 00:24:13,851
Okay?

396
00:24:14,721 --> 00:24:15,751
Yes.

397
00:24:18,121 --> 00:24:19,121
Don't cry.

398
00:24:28,601 --> 00:24:31,601
You must feel pretty bitter. What?
Is water going to be enough?

399
00:24:31,671 --> 00:24:34,271
You should have something stronger.
On the rocks, maybe?

400
00:24:38,711 --> 00:24:40,071
I can't even tease you.

401
00:24:40,281 --> 00:24:41,481
You really look like
you're struggling.

402
00:24:42,341 --> 00:24:43,341
Thanks for that.

403
00:25:07,941 --> 00:25:11,111
Why am I crying?
You'll jinx your uncle's new start.

404
00:25:30,591 --> 00:25:32,891
Honey, wake up.

405
00:25:35,831 --> 00:25:36,831
What?

406
00:25:37,371 --> 00:25:38,371
Se Ri.

407
00:25:39,431 --> 00:25:43,711
Here. Start with lukewarm water
to wake up your body rhythm.

408
00:25:43,841 --> 00:25:45,911
And let's do our stretches together,
all right?

409
00:25:46,471 --> 00:25:47,481
I love you.

410
00:25:58,351 --> 00:25:59,421
It was just a dream.

411
00:26:00,661 --> 00:26:02,621
Bucket, you idiot.

412
00:26:03,661 --> 00:26:07,101
After what happened with your mom,
all you think about is your wife.

413
00:26:07,601 --> 00:26:10,031
Are you even human?
What is wrong with you?

414
00:26:13,941 --> 00:26:15,201
I'll take that.

415
00:26:16,241 --> 00:26:17,911
You weren't in any pain last night,
were you?

416
00:26:18,641 --> 00:26:19,711
How'd you know?

417
00:26:20,311 --> 00:26:21,681
Were you watching me sleep again?

418
00:26:22,741 --> 00:26:23,751
Just a little.

419
00:26:27,821 --> 00:26:29,381
Who could that be so early?

420
00:26:30,551 --> 00:26:32,491
It's Bucket.

421
00:26:32,821 --> 00:26:33,861
Bucket?

422
00:26:34,121 --> 00:26:38,391
Dr. Han Seong Mi, I need the advice
of my primary physician.

423
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:42,301
He really gets
his money's worth out of me.

424
00:26:43,701 --> 00:26:44,701
Does it bother you?

425
00:26:45,201 --> 00:26:47,601
Bother me? It's my job.

426
00:26:48,101 --> 00:26:49,241
It's not a hassle?

427
00:26:49,501 --> 00:26:50,811
No, not at all.

428
00:26:52,971 --> 00:26:53,981
Why do you ask?

429
00:26:55,981 --> 00:26:58,111
Let's get you healthy again, okay?

430
00:26:58,381 --> 00:27:01,051
So you can go back
to being your old self.

431
00:27:01,651 --> 00:27:04,921
That's the best prescription
for you right now.

432
00:27:06,921 --> 00:27:08,821
Yes. I guess you're right.

433
00:27:09,961 --> 00:27:12,791
- All right, I'll give him the call.
- Take your time with the consult.

434
00:27:14,301 --> 00:27:15,301
Right.

435
00:27:19,501 --> 00:27:22,641
Sorry to call so early.
I mean, my apologies.

436
00:27:23,371 --> 00:27:25,271
I think something's
a little off with me.

437
00:27:25,871 --> 00:27:27,211
How so?

438
00:27:27,681 --> 00:27:29,381
My mother passed away,

439
00:27:30,211 --> 00:27:32,581
and I'm truly, deeply heartbroken,

440
00:27:33,251 --> 00:27:35,821
but all I can think about
is my estranged wife.

441
00:27:36,381 --> 00:27:38,051
Why am I even dreaming about her?

442
00:27:38,451 --> 00:27:40,761
That's
a completely natural reaction.

443
00:27:41,191 --> 00:27:42,621
Oh, really?

444
00:27:43,021 --> 00:27:44,061
Yes.

445
00:27:44,331 --> 00:27:48,701
When we experience a great loss,
we seek out the person we depend on.

446
00:27:50,261 --> 00:27:52,601
It sounds like your wife...

447
00:27:52,801 --> 00:27:57,041
was your rock,
the one who supported you.

448
00:27:57,211 --> 00:27:59,941
You're right.
I'm honestly terrified.

449
00:28:00,481 --> 00:28:02,241
If we keep living apart like this,

450
00:28:02,611 --> 00:28:04,011
I'm afraid we'll end up
separated for good.

451
00:28:04,981 --> 00:28:07,451
Shouldn't I do something?

452
00:28:08,681 --> 00:28:12,651
Reaching out while you're anxious
won't be good for either of you.

453
00:28:13,151 --> 00:28:14,391
Oh, is that right?

454
00:28:15,321 --> 00:28:16,321
I suppose that makes sense.

455
00:28:16,591 --> 00:28:20,731
Yes. Be considerate. Give her space
to spend time with her daughter.

456
00:28:20,831 --> 00:28:23,401
Just wait patiently and show her
you're still there for her.

457
00:28:24,031 --> 00:28:25,631
And don't be impatient.

458
00:28:26,401 --> 00:28:27,541
Don't be impatient.

459
00:28:28,801 --> 00:28:29,971
Don't rush it.

460
00:28:32,041 --> 00:28:34,641
I really do feel a lot better.

461
00:28:35,941 --> 00:28:38,981
Thank you so much, Doctor.

462
00:28:39,581 --> 00:28:42,421
I swear I will find a way
to repay you for this.

463
00:28:43,251 --> 00:28:44,251
Okay.

464
00:28:57,701 --> 00:28:58,701
Come in.

465
00:28:59,331 --> 00:29:00,331
Hey.

466
00:29:01,401 --> 00:29:03,271
Going out on a weekend?

467
00:29:03,501 --> 00:29:06,441
Yes, I have a pre-fitting
for the styling class today.

468
00:29:06,741 --> 00:29:09,441
- Why, Grandma?
- It's nothing.

469
00:29:10,911 --> 00:29:12,151
So when's your last day?

470
00:29:13,081 --> 00:29:14,081
Next week.

471
00:29:14,681 --> 00:29:17,421
Are you sure you won't regret it?

472
00:29:17,491 --> 00:29:19,391
You worked so hard
to get into that company.

473
00:29:19,751 --> 00:29:23,621
Grandma, I've made up my mind,
so please don't worry. Okay?

474
00:29:24,931 --> 00:29:28,361
I'm just uneasy that
I only gave your uncle his blessing.

475
00:29:28,431 --> 00:29:31,201
What's there to be uneasy about?
I'm completely over it.

476
00:29:32,271 --> 00:29:35,441
Look. Those photos and gifts
you saw back then?

477
00:29:35,501 --> 00:29:36,941
I've already marked them
to be thrown out.

478
00:29:43,041 --> 00:29:47,181
Grandma, once I quit my job,
how about you, Mom, and I...

479
00:29:47,251 --> 00:29:48,321
all go to a hot spring?

480
00:29:49,081 --> 00:29:51,551
I'd love that. Let's have a trip,
just the three of us.

481
00:29:51,821 --> 00:29:54,461
Okay. I'll find a place
with really great springs.

482
00:30:04,101 --> 00:30:07,301
I thought you were just winging it,
but you've opened a brunch spot.

483
00:30:07,841 --> 00:30:10,171
Grandfather actually really enjoys
food like this.

484
00:30:10,811 --> 00:30:12,771
Hyun Bin,
you're definitely husband material.

485
00:30:13,441 --> 00:30:17,251
- Eat up.
- Thanks, Hyun Bin. For being here.

486
00:30:17,451 --> 00:30:21,051
Of course. No more talk of leaving,
so don't you worry.

487
00:30:21,551 --> 00:30:22,551
You going to work today?

488
00:30:23,381 --> 00:30:27,091
I have to prep at the office.
Mother will be there too.

489
00:30:27,521 --> 00:30:28,721
Se Ri too?

490
00:30:29,161 --> 00:30:32,091
Dad, why? You're not thinking
of following her to work, are you?

491
00:30:33,091 --> 00:30:34,161
No.

492
00:30:34,161 --> 00:30:37,771
Dad. Don't use Grandma's passing...

493
00:30:37,831 --> 00:30:41,901
and just smooth things over
with Mom. Got it?

494
00:30:42,471 --> 00:30:43,471
I get it.

495
00:30:43,941 --> 00:30:45,771
I'm not going to rush things.
I promise.

496
00:30:46,111 --> 00:30:47,111
Don't worry.

497
00:30:51,811 --> 00:30:54,951
Mom, you look really down.

498
00:30:56,881 --> 00:30:58,191
What's wrong?

499
00:30:58,721 --> 00:31:00,151
Worried about the family?

500
00:31:01,061 --> 00:31:03,961
Everyone must be struggling
after the funeral,

501
00:31:04,331 --> 00:31:07,961
and I can't be there for them.
It's weighing on me.

502
00:31:08,961 --> 00:31:12,931
They're all doing fine without you,
Mom. Look.

503
00:31:17,371 --> 00:31:21,641
Eun Bin sent me this picture.
She says Hyun Bin made breakfast.

504
00:31:22,181 --> 00:31:23,541
Looks like
it's from a restaurant, right?

505
00:31:24,811 --> 00:31:25,811
It really does.

506
00:31:26,951 --> 00:31:29,451
Is there anything
our Hyun Bin can't do?

507
00:31:30,181 --> 00:31:32,091
We need to hurry up
and get Hyun Bin married,

508
00:31:32,491 --> 00:31:34,421
then maybe there'll be
a place for me too.

509
00:31:34,491 --> 00:31:38,531
Oh, Mom. You already have a place,
I keep telling you.

510
00:31:38,961 --> 00:31:41,761
- I'm not so sure.
- What are you talking about?

511
00:31:42,531 --> 00:31:46,031
You're going to be the absolute star
of the styling class today.

512
00:31:46,271 --> 00:31:50,341
Stop worrying about housework
and family,

513
00:31:50,401 --> 00:31:52,911
and start chasing
your own dreams. Okay?

514
00:31:52,971 --> 00:31:54,811
Please make your dreams come true.

515
00:31:57,181 --> 00:31:59,481
Okay, I will. Thank you.

516
00:31:59,511 --> 00:32:02,751
I'm going to stop by headquarters
and see Hyun Bin.

517
00:32:02,881 --> 00:32:05,051
- Okay, see you later.
- Okay.

518
00:32:09,591 --> 00:32:10,861
(Analysis of Newly Acquired
Branch Performance)

519
00:32:10,931 --> 00:32:11,931
(Three Key Improvement Strategies)

520
00:32:11,961 --> 00:32:13,691
(3H Acupressure Bed)

521
00:32:13,961 --> 00:32:18,231
Is my store
one of the underperforming ones?

522
00:32:19,571 --> 00:32:23,971
Your customer satisfaction ratings
aren't bad,

523
00:32:24,041 --> 00:32:27,311
but your purchase conversion rate
is a little on the low side.

524
00:32:28,211 --> 00:32:29,241
Oh, really?

525
00:32:30,281 --> 00:32:32,951
I thought I was working hard
and following the manual.

526
00:32:33,511 --> 00:32:38,391
You just took over the store,
so once you get more experience,

527
00:32:38,451 --> 00:32:40,921
I'm confident
the numbers will improve.

528
00:32:41,321 --> 00:32:45,661
In that case, would it be possible
to visit a top-performing store...

529
00:32:45,731 --> 00:32:50,601
to learn about their management
and sales strategies?

530
00:32:51,331 --> 00:32:52,331
Of course.

531
00:32:52,631 --> 00:32:55,071
I'll schedule that for you
right away.

532
00:33:07,951 --> 00:33:09,581
By the way, Ms. Gong.

533
00:33:09,951 --> 00:33:12,451
Is it confirmed that you're moving
to Ceviel?

534
00:33:13,121 --> 00:33:15,961
I have a friend at Ceviel,
and they hadn't heard anything.

535
00:33:16,221 --> 00:33:19,231
- Oh, it's not confirmed.
- What?

536
00:33:19,491 --> 00:33:20,491
Then what's the deal?

537
00:33:20,861 --> 00:33:22,931
You resigned before
it was even a done deal?

538
00:33:23,161 --> 00:33:26,731
Yes. If that falls through,
I'll just find something else.

539
00:33:29,501 --> 00:33:30,501
Director Yang!

540
00:33:30,771 --> 00:33:33,511
It seems Ms. Gong hasn't decided
where she's going next.

541
00:33:34,241 --> 00:33:35,241
And?

542
00:33:35,741 --> 00:33:36,741
What?

543
00:33:39,681 --> 00:33:41,781
It's almost time
for our VIP to arrive.

544
00:33:42,151 --> 00:33:45,491
- Yes, Director Yang. I'll be there.
- Okay.

545
00:33:53,331 --> 00:33:54,331
What am I going to do? What do I do?

546
00:33:54,661 --> 00:33:57,731
What do I do? What do I do!
Hyun Bin, listen.

547
00:33:57,931 --> 00:34:00,741
The thought of going on stage
is suddenly making me so nervous.

548
00:34:00,901 --> 00:34:02,641
Mother, you were
in a beauty pageant.

549
00:34:02,641 --> 00:34:04,941
Oh, please. That was ages ago.

550
00:34:10,751 --> 00:34:11,981
It's been a while.

551
00:34:13,451 --> 00:34:15,851
Thank you for helping us
with this event.

552
00:34:16,621 --> 00:34:17,621
Of course.

553
00:34:18,821 --> 00:34:22,891
- Is this the outfit I'm wearing?
- Yes, if you don't like it,

554
00:34:22,961 --> 00:34:24,761
I can show you another option.

555
00:34:25,031 --> 00:34:26,431
No, it's fine.

556
00:34:26,661 --> 00:34:31,571
We'll complete the look on-site
with accessories.

557
00:34:31,701 --> 00:34:33,171
All right, I'll leave you to it.

558
00:34:37,301 --> 00:34:40,371
- Ready for your fitting?
- Shall we?

559
00:34:41,841 --> 00:34:43,781
You're not putting pins in me again,
are you?

560
00:34:47,781 --> 00:34:50,651
I'm kidding. Let's go.

561
00:34:59,961 --> 00:35:03,931
Ms. Gong, there's something
I've been meaning to ask you.

562
00:35:04,301 --> 00:35:06,501
- Yes?
- It's about my son, Hyun Bin.

563
00:35:06,871 --> 00:35:11,811
Do you happen to know the person
that he has feelings for?

564
00:35:12,211 --> 00:35:13,441
I think it's someone from work.

565
00:35:17,211 --> 00:35:18,711
I really wouldn't know.

566
00:35:21,221 --> 00:35:24,021
- You know, don't you?
- Me? No.

567
00:35:24,351 --> 00:35:25,451
I think you know something.

568
00:35:26,091 --> 00:35:27,891
Could you please turn around?

569
00:35:32,331 --> 00:35:34,131
(Channel Success Strategy Summary)

570
00:35:35,401 --> 00:35:39,731
Wait, Mom was upset
seeing us get along?

571
00:35:40,431 --> 00:35:44,141
Yes. Maybe we went about this
the wrong way.

572
00:35:45,371 --> 00:35:47,741
It's because Mom finds
her whole sense of self-worth...

573
00:35:47,811 --> 00:35:50,441
only in taking care of her family.

574
00:35:51,011 --> 00:35:54,621
I'm worried they'll grow
even further apart at this rate.

575
00:35:54,781 --> 00:35:57,791
That won't happen. You know
Dad only has eyes for Mom.

576
00:35:58,291 --> 00:35:59,651
That's a relief.

577
00:36:00,321 --> 00:36:04,961
Let's think of a way to help him
show those feelings.

578
00:36:06,091 --> 00:36:09,661
But I must work on my business plan
for my YouTube channel.

579
00:36:09,761 --> 00:36:10,831
Come on.

580
00:36:10,931 --> 00:36:14,471
I have two things I must do
before I go back to America.

581
00:36:14,901 --> 00:36:15,901
Two things?

582
00:36:16,671 --> 00:36:21,081
One is making Mom and Dad make up.
What's the other one?

583
00:36:22,381 --> 00:36:23,481
I'm not telling you.

584
00:36:23,941 --> 00:36:27,511
Hey, you've got some nerve!
You're messing with the wrong one.

585
00:36:31,791 --> 00:36:34,661
Right. The friends I made
here in Korea,

586
00:36:34,721 --> 00:36:37,491
they're throwing me a goodbye party,
and you should come.

587
00:36:37,561 --> 00:36:38,831
Why would I go to that?

588
00:36:38,891 --> 00:36:42,261
Because I know
a famous creative director.

589
00:36:42,331 --> 00:36:43,401
Really?

590
00:36:44,201 --> 00:36:46,431
Well, if you're inviting me,
then I'd love to come.

591
00:36:47,271 --> 00:36:49,171
Yes! Is this how I get famous?

592
00:36:50,101 --> 00:36:51,771
I'm going to hit
a million subscribers.

593
00:36:52,011 --> 00:36:54,581
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

594
00:37:00,921 --> 00:37:03,421
What are you doing out here?
You should be resting.

595
00:37:04,181 --> 00:37:05,321
I'm fine.

596
00:37:05,951 --> 00:37:08,821
You must've had a tough time alone
while I was gone,

597
00:37:08,961 --> 00:37:11,391
so I feel bad for making you come in
every day without a break.

598
00:37:11,931 --> 00:37:12,931
By the way,

599
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:17,061
your families are meeting tomorrow?
Congratulations.

600
00:37:17,971 --> 00:37:19,401
There's nothing
to congratulate me about.

601
00:37:20,171 --> 00:37:24,541
We haven't found your grandpa yet.
I don't even know if this is right.

602
00:37:24,841 --> 00:37:28,141
Everyone's working hard to find him.
Director Yang is a big help, too.

603
00:37:28,911 --> 00:37:29,911
Right.

604
00:37:30,741 --> 00:37:32,781
Hey, a little more to the right.
To the right.

605
00:37:32,881 --> 00:37:34,721
And a little higher from there. Up.

606
00:37:34,781 --> 00:37:38,021
- Yes, right there.
- Hey, it's too high. I can't see.

607
00:37:38,091 --> 00:37:39,891
Trust me. This is so that
people can see it from far away.

608
00:37:39,891 --> 00:37:41,361
- A little more.
- If you see someone like him,

609
00:37:41,361 --> 00:37:42,361
please give us a call.

610
00:37:42,691 --> 00:37:44,021
I'm telling you,
even I can't see it.

611
00:37:44,091 --> 00:37:45,661
Hey, I told you, this is how
people will see it from far away.

612
00:37:46,291 --> 00:37:47,801
Yes, that's it.

613
00:37:48,461 --> 00:37:49,531
Thank you.

614
00:37:49,861 --> 00:37:52,101
- He's our father.
- If you see anyone similar...

615
00:37:52,831 --> 00:37:53,871
Yes, thank you.

616
00:37:53,871 --> 00:37:55,141
We're looking for a missing person.

617
00:37:55,201 --> 00:37:56,471
If you happen to see him...

618
00:37:56,471 --> 00:37:57,571
(Missing Person)

619
00:37:58,611 --> 00:38:00,981
- What do you think you're doing?
- Yes, sir. We're very sorry.

620
00:38:01,081 --> 00:38:02,081
- We're sorry, it's just...
- We were just...

621
00:38:02,141 --> 00:38:03,141
It's an urgent family matter...

622
00:38:03,341 --> 00:38:04,381
Hello.

623
00:38:04,381 --> 00:38:08,581
We're looking for our father.
Can we please put up a few of these?

624
00:38:09,251 --> 00:38:10,951
(Missing Person)

625
00:38:11,091 --> 00:38:14,561
- Just don't put up too many.
- Okay. Thank you so much.

626
00:38:15,661 --> 00:38:17,791
Thank you.
We appreciate you allowing this.

627
00:38:17,861 --> 00:38:18,931
Yes, thank you very much.

628
00:38:19,231 --> 00:38:21,861
If you see anyone resembling him,
please give us a call.

629
00:38:21,931 --> 00:38:24,671
- Sir, could you look at this?
- Thank you.

630
00:38:24,731 --> 00:38:26,831
- If you could give us a call...
- Here you go.

631
00:38:29,141 --> 00:38:32,241
Hey, Dong Ik.
You couldn't even rest this weekend.

632
00:38:32,311 --> 00:38:33,941
I feel terrible
making you go through all this.

633
00:38:34,511 --> 00:38:36,241
He's right. We can handle the rest,

634
00:38:36,781 --> 00:38:39,111
- so go get a bite and head home.
- Yes, you should.

635
00:38:39,181 --> 00:38:40,181
No, it's fine.

636
00:38:40,711 --> 00:38:41,951
We'll finish faster
if we do it together.

637
00:38:43,421 --> 00:38:44,421
Right.

638
00:38:45,351 --> 00:38:47,821
Dae Han. Here.

639
00:38:48,961 --> 00:38:49,961
What's this?

640
00:38:50,161 --> 00:38:53,061
Get yourself a nice suit
for the family meeting tomorrow.

641
00:38:56,301 --> 00:39:00,331
- No, it's fine. I have a suit.
- Come on, just take it.

642
00:39:01,271 --> 00:39:03,271
What's with this guy? Just take it.

643
00:39:05,041 --> 00:39:06,041
Thanks. I really appreciate it.

644
00:39:06,311 --> 00:39:07,311
Don't mention it.

645
00:39:07,711 --> 00:39:10,481
Don't we need to go to Seongdam?

646
00:39:10,681 --> 00:39:13,581
Officer Jeong and Jin Ah
already went there.

647
00:39:13,881 --> 00:39:15,481
- They did?
- Yes.

648
00:39:15,821 --> 00:39:17,451
That's good of them.

649
00:39:18,521 --> 00:39:19,751
(Seongdam Real Estate)

650
00:39:19,821 --> 00:39:20,821
Hello?

651
00:39:21,821 --> 00:39:22,821
Did you find anything out?

652
00:39:23,361 --> 00:39:27,631
Yes, a man matching the description
was at the back of the tailor shop.

653
00:39:27,901 --> 00:39:30,461
- Really?
- Yes, but he wasn't alone.

654
00:39:30,831 --> 00:39:33,431
Apparently,
a woman was living with him.

655
00:39:33,831 --> 00:39:35,541
What? A woman?

656
00:39:36,541 --> 00:39:40,041
Wait. So the woman he was seeing
was someone else?

657
00:39:40,871 --> 00:39:44,551
I'll see if it was an affair
or something crime-related.

658
00:39:44,881 --> 00:39:46,051
Then you should let her know
right away.

659
00:39:46,411 --> 00:39:47,851
No, no.

660
00:39:48,451 --> 00:39:52,591
If we reveal too much,
they might catch on and disappear.

661
00:39:53,121 --> 00:39:55,891
First, let's map out their movements
from where they were spotted,

662
00:39:56,091 --> 00:39:58,591
then we can ask the control center
to preserve the CCTV footage...

663
00:39:58,861 --> 00:40:01,761
and request access to view it.
I think that's our best move.

664
00:40:06,771 --> 00:40:07,771
What?

665
00:40:09,171 --> 00:40:10,171
That was so cool.

666
00:40:12,511 --> 00:40:16,511
But are we sure
this is how we're spending our date?

667
00:40:16,611 --> 00:40:20,281
What's wrong with it?
I'm channeling my inner detective,

668
00:40:20,381 --> 00:40:22,081
and can't you tell
I'm having an absolute blast?

669
00:40:24,651 --> 00:40:25,651
What?

670
00:40:26,021 --> 00:40:27,021
You're adorable.

671
00:40:27,751 --> 00:40:30,161
Come on.

672
00:40:31,561 --> 00:40:32,561
Come on, let's go.

673
00:40:32,931 --> 00:40:33,961
- Should we grab a bite first?
- Yes.

674
00:40:37,761 --> 00:40:38,771
Here you go.

675
00:40:38,831 --> 00:40:40,201
(Missing Person)

676
00:40:40,301 --> 00:40:41,301
Just like you always do,

677
00:40:41,701 --> 00:40:43,441
when you're collecting scrap paper
late at night,

678
00:40:44,971 --> 00:40:47,941
or early in the morning,
grab every flyer you see.

679
00:40:48,011 --> 00:40:52,251
- Okay.
- And make sure no one notices you.

680
00:40:52,481 --> 00:40:54,281
Don't you worry.

681
00:40:57,951 --> 00:40:58,951
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

682
00:41:06,661 --> 00:41:07,661
Mother.

683
00:41:08,631 --> 00:41:12,771
- Yes?
- Why are you lost in thought?

684
00:41:15,101 --> 00:41:19,641
I'm wondering if we did something
to make someone resent us.

685
00:41:20,271 --> 00:41:22,211
We haven't, right?
I can't think of anything.

686
00:41:22,981 --> 00:41:25,981
There could be something
that I just don't remember.

687
00:41:27,151 --> 00:41:31,721
I'm going to use all my connections
to get his story in the media.

688
00:41:32,351 --> 00:41:37,061
That misunderstanding kept us quiet,
but we don't have to anymore, right?

689
00:41:38,761 --> 00:41:39,961
But what if...

690
00:41:40,931 --> 00:41:42,831
What if he really
has lost his memory?

691
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:44,901
If he were to get it back,

692
00:41:45,631 --> 00:41:47,271
don't you think he'd come home?

693
00:41:48,441 --> 00:41:49,571
It's possible.

694
00:41:50,171 --> 00:41:51,311
Oh, dear.

695
00:41:52,641 --> 00:41:55,841
Just thinking about where he is
and what he must be going through...

696
00:41:57,481 --> 00:41:58,811
Mother.

697
00:41:59,281 --> 00:42:00,981
No, it's just...
It's so heartbreaking.

698
00:42:02,251 --> 00:42:04,151
To think that he's lost
so many memories...

699
00:42:04,891 --> 00:42:07,851
and is out there living,
not knowing a thing...

700
00:42:09,591 --> 00:42:12,991
Mother, look.
The show's starting. Okay?

701
00:42:29,411 --> 00:42:30,411
(Onjeong Market)

702
00:42:31,281 --> 00:42:32,881
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

703
00:42:33,551 --> 00:42:35,451
Alright, great work, everyone.

704
00:42:35,851 --> 00:42:38,751
Well, here's to a healthy day,

705
00:42:39,051 --> 00:42:42,121
and a prosperous one.
See you all tomorrow!

706
00:42:42,191 --> 00:42:45,161
- See you tomorrow!
- Gong Myeong...

707
00:42:46,261 --> 00:42:49,661
- Jeong Dae Han...
- The environmental cleanup...

708
00:42:49,731 --> 00:42:51,971
- Clinic.
- will now begin.

709
00:42:52,031 --> 00:42:54,001
- Okay.
- Yes, go ahead. Yes.

710
00:42:55,471 --> 00:42:56,871
Sunny...

711
00:42:57,501 --> 00:42:58,541
Korean Medicine Clinic.

712
00:43:10,381 --> 00:43:12,851
Even when I'm gone, take your meds
when the alarm goes off.

713
00:43:13,251 --> 00:43:16,561
You know you could die
if you don't. Got it?

714
00:43:40,111 --> 00:43:42,251
Uncle, I can't make it today.

715
00:43:42,481 --> 00:43:46,121
You know why, right?
Because the boss has to be there.

716
00:43:47,221 --> 00:43:48,891
Got it. Look after the shop for me.

717
00:43:49,991 --> 00:43:52,861
Ju Ah, are you going
to your uncle's event?

718
00:43:53,161 --> 00:43:54,161
Well...

719
00:43:54,561 --> 00:43:58,101
As long as Uncle won't be upset,
I'd rather not go.

720
00:43:58,431 --> 00:44:01,701
Why would I be upset?
It'd be awkward with you all there.

721
00:44:02,141 --> 00:44:03,241
Then I'm passing too.

722
00:44:03,501 --> 00:44:06,041
Gosh, I don't think I can handle
running into her twice in one day.

723
00:44:06,771 --> 00:44:08,511
- Twice?
- Why?

724
00:44:08,581 --> 00:44:11,211
Director Yang's mother has
her styling class today.

725
00:44:11,551 --> 00:44:15,051
Yesterday, she brought up that time
I pricked her with a pin.

726
00:44:15,521 --> 00:44:16,521
She did?

727
00:44:19,221 --> 00:44:23,061
So can everyone please try
to not stress Mom out today?

728
00:44:23,261 --> 00:44:25,261
You know how unpredictable
she can be.

729
00:44:26,391 --> 00:44:30,261
Then you shouldn't go today.
We can just go without you.

730
00:44:30,331 --> 00:44:33,331
He's right. If you're uncomfortable,
you don't have to come.

731
00:44:33,631 --> 00:44:37,201
Of course I have to go.
What are you talking about?

732
00:44:48,651 --> 00:44:51,221
Oh my. Gosh, that scared me.

733
00:45:02,161 --> 00:45:03,801
(The nights are long here.
Sometimes, thoughts of you linger.)

734
00:45:03,861 --> 00:45:04,931
(I was the shortest kid
at school today.)

735
00:45:05,001 --> 00:45:06,071
(It's okay. I'll be cool
when I grow up.)

736
00:45:07,371 --> 00:45:08,371
(It rained today.
The rain here is warm.)

737
00:45:08,441 --> 00:45:09,501
(But the rain smelled
just like Onjeong.)

738
00:45:13,211 --> 00:45:14,211
I can't believe this kid...

739
00:45:14,781 --> 00:45:17,481
Why keep this for all this time?

740
00:45:19,281 --> 00:45:21,981
They say a man never forgets
his first love.

741
00:45:23,321 --> 00:45:25,321
Gosh, whatever.

742
00:45:48,041 --> 00:45:49,241
Wait a minute...

743
00:45:49,841 --> 00:45:50,911
What is this?

744
00:46:01,521 --> 00:46:05,061
Hello. I'm Gong Ju Ah, your host
for today's styling class.

745
00:46:10,561 --> 00:46:14,201
Please sit back and enjoy the style
of this season's new collection.

746
00:46:14,731 --> 00:46:18,211
- Nice. Here they come.
- Here they come.

747
00:46:26,881 --> 00:46:29,481
There's someone else
I want to marry.

748
00:46:47,001 --> 00:46:48,401
But I thought you said
there's a woman you like.

749
00:46:48,401 --> 00:46:49,571
You're not going to marry her?

750
00:46:49,801 --> 00:46:52,571
No. I figured you'd all be
against it anyway.

751
00:46:55,511 --> 00:46:57,841
I can't believe it.
It was Gong Ju Ah all along.

752
00:46:57,911 --> 00:47:02,351
FG's first outfit is very mobile
and versatile for everyday wear.

753
00:47:02,581 --> 00:47:04,251
It's part of our sports-casual line.

754
00:47:18,061 --> 00:47:22,341
The second outfit is a resort look
inspired by the Mediterranean.

755
00:47:22,771 --> 00:47:26,771
With diverse patterns and materials,
it's a look for resorts or fields,

756
00:47:26,941 --> 00:47:28,981
making it a truly versatile style.

757
00:47:36,251 --> 00:47:40,721
And now, we'd like to invite a guest
from our audience up on stage...

758
00:47:40,791 --> 00:47:44,491
so we can demonstrate
styling in person.

759
00:47:45,261 --> 00:47:47,761
Ma'am, would you mind coming up here
for a moment?

760
00:47:49,561 --> 00:47:50,601
Oh, right.

761
00:47:58,911 --> 00:48:02,181
Your current outfit is already
very stylish.

762
00:48:02,641 --> 00:48:04,681
Now, if we just add this here...

763
00:48:05,611 --> 00:48:06,611
There.

764
00:48:11,651 --> 00:48:14,721
See how adding just one hat
can completely change the vibe?

765
00:48:15,791 --> 00:48:18,861
And if we add a statement bag.

766
00:48:18,861 --> 00:48:19,961
There.

767
00:48:23,601 --> 00:48:24,601
There we go.

768
00:48:25,231 --> 00:48:28,031
You can create
a much more sophisticated look.

769
00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:31,941
We need to talk later.

770
00:48:32,811 --> 00:48:34,011
Please strike a pose for us.

771
00:48:43,221 --> 00:48:46,121
Was something making you
uncomfortable?

772
00:48:47,251 --> 00:48:51,091
I would've preferred to discuss this
at a coffee shop,

773
00:48:51,791 --> 00:48:53,091
but I guess we're doing this here?

774
00:48:53,531 --> 00:48:55,031
I'm still on the clock.

775
00:48:57,431 --> 00:48:58,431
Ms. Gong.

776
00:49:00,631 --> 00:49:01,771
Are you dating my Hyun Bin?

777
00:49:07,141 --> 00:49:08,141
We broke up.

778
00:49:08,681 --> 00:49:10,041
So you're admitting you were dating.

779
00:49:11,651 --> 00:49:13,781
Then why didn't you answer me
when I asked you yesterday?

780
00:49:14,911 --> 00:49:18,851
If you have any questions,
I suggest you ask Director Yang.

781
00:49:20,991 --> 00:49:22,591
So your family...

782
00:49:24,261 --> 00:49:25,791
knew you two were dating, I take it?

783
00:49:27,761 --> 00:49:28,961
I see.

784
00:49:29,361 --> 00:49:32,131
So that's why you had my son
chauffeuring you all around.

785
00:49:32,801 --> 00:49:34,801
Right. Now it all makes sense.

786
00:49:35,741 --> 00:49:38,571
And what about your mother
becoming a model?

787
00:49:38,911 --> 00:49:40,911
Did you beg my Hyun Bin
to arrange that, too?

788
00:49:42,341 --> 00:49:44,041
You should ask Director Yang.

789
00:49:45,511 --> 00:49:47,781
I'm the one talking
to you right now.

790
00:49:48,251 --> 00:49:49,881
Where do you think you're going
when an elder is speaking?

791
00:49:51,181 --> 00:49:52,191
Mother!

792
00:50:03,661 --> 00:50:06,201
Ask me. I'll answer your questions.

793
00:50:06,771 --> 00:50:07,771
Hyun Bin.

794
00:50:08,771 --> 00:50:10,101
Is it true you two were dating?

795
00:50:11,041 --> 00:50:12,841
Were you planning to leave Korea
because of her?

796
00:50:13,171 --> 00:50:16,681
Don't refer to her like that.
We are at a place of business.

797
00:50:16,741 --> 00:50:17,841
Then why did you break up?

798
00:50:18,781 --> 00:50:20,981
What on earth did her family do?

799
00:50:21,181 --> 00:50:23,781
Did they make you run their errands
and then reject you?

800
00:50:24,051 --> 00:50:26,251
We've already broken up. It's over.

801
00:50:26,391 --> 00:50:29,461
I'm just so angry.
To think that because of Ms. Gong,

802
00:50:29,521 --> 00:50:31,831
to think you'd leave this family,
all because of Ms. Gong.

803
00:50:32,031 --> 00:50:34,361
No. In fact,

804
00:50:34,431 --> 00:50:36,731
Ms. Gong is the one who convinced me
to stay with my family.

805
00:50:37,101 --> 00:50:38,101
So...

806
00:50:38,771 --> 00:50:41,271
So you'll keep seeing each other
at the same company?

807
00:50:41,501 --> 00:50:42,671
Ms. Gong is resigning.

808
00:50:43,071 --> 00:50:47,171
Today is her last day.
We won't see each other, so drop it.

809
00:50:47,311 --> 00:50:49,481
What do you mean you won't meet?

810
00:50:49,481 --> 00:50:51,951
There's the family dinner later,

811
00:50:52,111 --> 00:50:56,321
and once Dong Suk gets married,
you'll see each other more often.

812
00:50:56,381 --> 00:50:58,021
Then I just won't go!

813
00:50:59,121 --> 00:51:03,221
- Hyun Bin, you...
- I said I'll never see her again!

814
00:51:03,661 --> 00:51:04,661
Is that good enough for you?

815
00:51:24,111 --> 00:51:25,111
Yes, Vice President.

816
00:51:26,781 --> 00:51:29,021
Where did you run off to
in the middle of the event?

817
00:51:31,991 --> 00:51:33,851
Director Baek's been making
some strange moves.

818
00:51:34,891 --> 00:51:37,491
Why is he meeting so many people
from the fashion industry?

819
00:51:38,321 --> 00:51:40,961
Why is he meeting with the heads
of overseas fashion brands?

820
00:51:42,361 --> 00:51:45,401
This seems like more than a plan
to take down the Fashion Division.

821
00:51:45,571 --> 00:51:46,571
My point exactly.

822
00:51:48,101 --> 00:51:49,601
Don't you have anyone on the inside
with Director Baek?

823
00:51:50,601 --> 00:51:51,601
Me?

824
00:51:54,041 --> 00:51:56,841
You're a vice president and yet,

825
00:51:57,241 --> 00:51:59,011
what have you done all this time
without anyone on your side?

826
00:52:00,511 --> 00:52:02,251
Have you ever seen me
do anything right?

827
00:52:02,921 --> 00:52:04,721
Gosh, why are you grilling me
about it now?

828
00:52:06,051 --> 00:52:07,051
My gosh.

829
00:52:08,891 --> 00:52:14,061
What are you talking about?
You want me to come here? Why?

830
00:52:14,191 --> 00:52:17,801
Gosh, just do what I tell you.
Why all the questions?

831
00:52:19,401 --> 00:52:21,431
But, Director Yang.

832
00:52:22,401 --> 00:52:26,671
Take a good look. Okay?
I'm Mr. Park, not Ms. Gong.

833
00:52:29,011 --> 00:52:30,181
Taehan's Fashion Division...

834
00:52:30,481 --> 00:52:32,081
What does it mean to you, Mr. Park?

835
00:52:32,781 --> 00:52:33,781
That's so random.

836
00:52:34,951 --> 00:52:38,751
Well, I'd say
we're one and the same.

837
00:52:39,221 --> 00:52:42,561
Then you'd be willing to do anything
for the Fashion Division, right?

838
00:52:43,391 --> 00:52:44,421
What?

839
00:52:44,421 --> 00:52:47,061
You're the only person I can trust,
Mr. Park.

840
00:52:47,261 --> 00:52:51,501
Oh my! What's with the sudden
change in tune?

841
00:52:52,001 --> 00:52:53,301
Work with me on something.

842
00:52:54,171 --> 00:52:55,201
On what?

843
00:53:00,841 --> 00:53:01,881
What?

844
00:53:01,881 --> 00:53:05,281
If you know your enemy and yourself,
you can win a hundred battles.

845
00:53:06,451 --> 00:53:09,421
Seriously, what do you want from me?
You're scaring me.

846
00:53:13,621 --> 00:53:16,061
- The vice president's guy friend?
- Yes.

847
00:53:16,821 --> 00:53:19,091
But it's not just
the Vice President.

848
00:53:19,591 --> 00:53:21,791
He also appears to be very close
with Director Yang Hyun Bin.

849
00:53:22,231 --> 00:53:24,961
He's in the know,
and since he's so sociable,

850
00:53:25,431 --> 00:53:27,231
So at the company,
they call him Mr. Connections.

851
00:53:28,001 --> 00:53:29,001
Never mind that.

852
00:53:29,601 --> 00:53:31,871
You're sure there's nothing special
going on with Hye Su?

853
00:53:32,371 --> 00:53:33,371
Yes, sir.

854
00:53:34,211 --> 00:53:35,641
So he's a nobody. Fine.

855
00:53:36,541 --> 00:53:38,751
And what do his parents do?

856
00:53:39,851 --> 00:53:42,251
There's no information available
on his father.

857
00:53:42,751 --> 00:53:43,751
Passed away?

858
00:53:44,121 --> 00:53:47,791
His HR file says he doesn't know
who his father is.

859
00:53:48,151 --> 00:53:49,361
That's what's on file.

860
00:53:50,191 --> 00:53:52,891
He probably was raised by
his single mother, Kim Hyang Sook,

861
00:53:53,461 --> 00:53:54,691
and had a difficult upbringing.

862
00:53:55,601 --> 00:53:58,771
So she could've been an unwed mother
and he was born out of wedlock?

863
00:53:59,231 --> 00:54:00,231
That is correct.

864
00:54:04,441 --> 00:54:06,041
(Taehan Group)

865
00:54:06,711 --> 00:54:08,371
You should've led with that!

866
00:54:09,041 --> 00:54:10,041
My apologies.

867
00:54:19,251 --> 00:54:22,921
Chairman, you can't eat any more.
Something terrible could happen.

868
00:54:30,131 --> 00:54:32,371
- That boy.
- Who, sir?

869
00:54:32,771 --> 00:54:33,831
The one who brought this for you?

870
00:54:34,401 --> 00:54:35,401
He's a spitting image.

871
00:54:36,101 --> 00:54:37,101
Of whom?

872
00:54:39,011 --> 00:54:40,071
Hyang Sook.

873
00:54:41,111 --> 00:54:42,111
Kim Hyang Sook.

874
00:54:43,241 --> 00:54:46,251
(Taehan Group)

875
00:54:50,621 --> 00:54:51,681
Mr. Park Jun Hyeok.

876
00:55:00,391 --> 00:55:03,101
I'm honored you know my name,
Director Baek.

877
00:55:03,601 --> 00:55:06,431
How could I not?
You're key to the Fashion Division.

878
00:55:07,601 --> 00:55:10,671
Thank you for your great interest
in our Fashion Division.

879
00:55:10,741 --> 00:55:12,141
We're truly grateful.

880
00:55:14,711 --> 00:55:16,941
I hear you're close with the VP
and Director Yang.

881
00:55:17,341 --> 00:55:18,981
You and I should get close as well.

882
00:55:19,851 --> 00:55:21,481
Of course, Director Baek.
It would be my honor.

883
00:55:21,781 --> 00:55:23,851
Perhaps we could grab
a coffee sometime?

884
00:55:26,721 --> 00:55:28,121
Sure, why not?

885
00:55:29,321 --> 00:55:30,321
Great.

886
00:55:39,101 --> 00:55:41,631
Mom, come on, smile. Okay?

887
00:55:42,401 --> 00:55:43,401
Okay.

888
00:55:43,871 --> 00:55:45,841
No pain, no gain!
It's a blessing! You got this!

889
00:55:46,441 --> 00:55:47,441
Let's do this.

890
00:55:52,881 --> 00:55:53,981
Father.

891
00:55:54,681 --> 00:55:55,751
I'm heading out.

892
00:55:56,151 --> 00:56:00,051
- Leaving already?
- Yes, Se Ri should be home early.

893
00:56:00,851 --> 00:56:02,761
Dong Suk will come by
to pick you up.

894
00:56:03,091 --> 00:56:04,091
All right, you go on ahead.

895
00:56:05,121 --> 00:56:08,331
- Go on, hurry and see Se Ri.
- Okay.

896
00:56:17,341 --> 00:56:18,341
Gosh, what's wrong with me?

897
00:56:20,811 --> 00:56:22,741
- All set?
- Hey, Jeong Han.

898
00:56:23,081 --> 00:56:25,651
Man, I'm getting a little nervous.

899
00:56:25,751 --> 00:56:28,411
What's there to be nervous about?
Hey, hey. Let me fix your tie.

900
00:56:28,481 --> 00:56:29,481
There you go.

901
00:56:30,121 --> 00:56:31,121
Oh my!

902
00:56:31,651 --> 00:56:35,821
Hey! Looking sharp, little brother.
So handsome!

903
00:56:36,921 --> 00:56:40,531
- Come on. Put on your jacket. Here.
- Why am I trembling like this?

904
00:56:40,661 --> 00:56:43,531
- Why are you shaking? Come on.
- Gosh, I'm losing my mind.

905
00:56:45,331 --> 00:56:46,331
Nice, very nice.

906
00:56:47,571 --> 00:56:48,571
Gosh!

907
00:56:49,401 --> 00:56:50,401
Oh my!

908
00:56:50,701 --> 00:56:54,011
- Mom, I'm home.
- Gosh! You're back early.

909
00:56:54,111 --> 00:56:57,141
Yes, I finished my work early.
But Mom, what's wrong?

910
00:56:57,381 --> 00:57:00,651
- Are you in pain? Are you?
- No, no. It's nothing.

911
00:57:01,081 --> 00:57:03,781
I have a doctor's appointment.
I'll just go quickly and then rest.

912
00:57:04,981 --> 00:57:07,321
Can't you just stay home
and rest today?

913
00:57:07,691 --> 00:57:09,261
How could I do that?

914
00:57:10,121 --> 00:57:12,331
Don't say a word to your grandma,
okay?

915
00:57:12,931 --> 00:57:15,231
It's a special day.
I don't want to worry everyone.

916
00:57:16,901 --> 00:57:19,401
Then I'll go with you.
I'll be there to look after you.

917
00:57:20,931 --> 00:57:23,641
Can you handle seeing
Director Yang's mother twice today?

918
00:57:52,631 --> 00:57:55,901
I'm the one
who found this restaurant.

919
00:57:56,771 --> 00:57:57,771
What do you think?

920
00:57:58,601 --> 00:57:59,741
Looks like...

921
00:58:00,341 --> 00:58:01,771
you don't need me anymore.

922
00:58:02,741 --> 00:58:04,141
You do just fine on your own.

923
00:58:04,881 --> 00:58:08,311
No, how could you say that?

924
00:58:09,321 --> 00:58:11,751
Listen, Se Ri...

925
00:58:13,321 --> 00:58:14,321
Did you...

926
00:58:14,991 --> 00:58:15,991
by any chance...

927
00:58:16,361 --> 00:58:19,261
know that Hyun Bin and Gong Ju Ah
used to date?

928
00:58:21,261 --> 00:58:22,261
They did?

929
00:58:23,901 --> 00:58:25,331
I had no idea.

930
00:58:26,571 --> 00:58:27,671
Then why don't you seem surprised?

931
00:58:27,901 --> 00:58:32,371
Is it that surprising?

932
00:58:32,971 --> 00:58:35,841
Now that our families
are on good terms,

933
00:58:36,711 --> 00:58:38,881
I don't see
why it should be a problem.

934
00:58:41,351 --> 00:58:42,921
So now, my opinion...

935
00:58:43,451 --> 00:58:45,151
means nothing to you.

936
00:58:46,491 --> 00:58:49,421
No, you know that's not true.

937
00:58:50,591 --> 00:58:51,721
Well...

938
00:58:52,361 --> 00:58:54,691
Se Ri, I'm just going
to use the restroom.

939
00:59:09,441 --> 00:59:10,781
(Dong Suk)

940
00:59:14,781 --> 00:59:15,821
Yes, Dong Suk.

941
00:59:16,721 --> 00:59:18,021
We've arrived.

942
00:59:19,221 --> 00:59:21,051
Okay, be careful on your way.

943
00:59:23,321 --> 00:59:25,191
(Today, Han Seong Mi)

944
00:59:28,261 --> 00:59:29,801
(Yesterday, Han Seong Mi)

945
00:59:29,861 --> 00:59:31,361
(Saturday, May 16, Han Seong Mi)

946
00:59:33,401 --> 00:59:34,401
What's this?

947
00:59:34,971 --> 00:59:36,271
Dr. Han Seong Mi?

948
00:59:37,101 --> 00:59:38,771
Why were there so many
calls with her?

949
00:59:42,211 --> 00:59:43,211
This is annoying.

950
00:59:48,851 --> 00:59:50,521
You're here already.

951
00:59:50,881 --> 00:59:52,391
Yes, hello.

952
01:00:06,671 --> 01:00:08,301
Thank you for sending her off...

953
01:00:09,971 --> 01:00:13,311
so that she won't be lonely
on her journey.

954
01:00:14,311 --> 01:00:15,471
Of course.

955
01:00:16,411 --> 01:00:18,781
Let's put what's happened
in the past behind us,

956
01:00:20,911 --> 01:00:22,921
and for the sake of the children,

957
01:00:23,981 --> 01:00:26,891
I hope we can support
one another from now on.

958
01:00:27,191 --> 01:00:28,521
- Yes.
- Yes.

959
01:00:29,161 --> 01:00:33,091
For today, I just want to wish
them both a happy future together.

960
01:00:34,161 --> 01:00:37,961
So, when were you thinking
of having the wedding ceremony?

961
01:00:38,261 --> 01:00:39,271
Dong Ik.

962
01:00:39,731 --> 01:00:41,101
A wedding?
What are you talking about?

963
01:00:41,371 --> 01:00:42,741
It's a second marriage
for both of us.

964
01:00:43,941 --> 01:00:47,541
Still, you can't just decide
that on your own.

965
01:00:47,971 --> 01:00:50,441
Dong Suk might want one, you know.

966
01:00:51,311 --> 01:00:52,511
No, it's not like that, Se Ri.

967
01:00:53,181 --> 01:00:54,881
We've already talked about this.

968
01:00:55,451 --> 01:00:59,591
Then how about a small, simple
gathering with just the family?

969
01:01:01,091 --> 01:01:02,521
That sounds like a great idea.

970
01:01:04,121 --> 01:01:05,161
Yes, that sounds good.

971
01:01:05,731 --> 01:01:09,261
- Let's do that, then.
- Are you sure that's okay?

972
01:01:10,461 --> 01:01:14,131
I'm just wondering
if we should find Gi Cheol first.

973
01:01:15,271 --> 01:01:18,571
I think they should do
whatever they're comfortable with.

974
01:01:20,771 --> 01:01:22,271
I agree as well.

975
01:01:24,181 --> 01:01:25,481
What do you think?

976
01:01:42,131 --> 01:01:43,201
My husband and I...

977
01:01:43,831 --> 01:01:45,001
are separated. You knew that, right?

978
01:01:46,471 --> 01:01:48,701
Didn't you know we split up...

979
01:01:48,701 --> 01:01:50,701
because he hired
a PI to investigate me?

980
01:01:51,041 --> 01:01:52,611
Especially since you two talk
on the phone so much.

981
01:01:54,171 --> 01:01:56,081
Are you acting this way...

982
01:01:56,081 --> 01:01:57,441
because I've been talking
to Dr. Yang?

983
01:01:57,941 --> 01:01:58,981
Yes.

984
01:01:59,451 --> 01:02:02,521
Why are you on the phone
with my husband so much?

985
01:02:02,981 --> 01:02:05,251
You have quite a nasty habit.

986
01:02:05,921 --> 01:02:09,051
You should ask your husband
about that, not me.

987
01:02:09,121 --> 01:02:11,191
And for the record,
you've got it all wrong.

988
01:02:11,591 --> 01:02:14,091
Dr. Yang was struggling,
so I was just counseling him.

989
01:02:15,031 --> 01:02:16,031
Counseling?

990
01:02:16,901 --> 01:02:20,301
So I suppose when psychiatrists talk
to another's husband day and night,

991
01:02:20,371 --> 01:02:22,771
do they call private phone calls
"counseling?"

992
01:02:23,101 --> 01:02:26,111
- What did you say?
- Using your profession...

993
01:02:26,111 --> 01:02:27,741
as an excuse to dig into
other people's private lives.

994
01:02:28,011 --> 01:02:29,141
Did you have fun?

995
01:02:29,741 --> 01:02:32,681
I was just giving some advice
to an emotionally drained friend,

996
01:02:32,981 --> 01:02:34,451
and you twist it into
something like this.

997
01:02:34,781 --> 01:02:37,721
It's a pity your understanding
is so shallow.

998
01:02:39,051 --> 01:02:40,151
So pretentious.

999
01:02:40,421 --> 01:02:41,421
What did you say?

1000
01:02:41,691 --> 01:02:45,261
Forget it. Why am I wasting my time
arguing with a patient?

1001
01:02:46,361 --> 01:02:48,631
Excuse me? Seriously?

1002
01:02:49,701 --> 01:02:52,671
Seriously, I can't
take this anymore.

1003
01:02:53,071 --> 01:02:54,201
(Occupied, Vacant)

1004
01:02:57,041 --> 01:02:58,601
You think you can say
whatever you want?

1005
01:03:41,881 --> 01:03:44,851
(Recipe For Love)

1006
01:03:45,051 --> 01:03:48,251
I'd love for Dong Suk
to come live at our house.

1007
01:03:48,321 --> 01:03:49,791
- No!
- Right, since there's...

1008
01:03:49,791 --> 01:03:50,961
no room for Ji Hu either.

1009
01:03:50,961 --> 01:03:52,061
How about our house?

1010
01:03:52,261 --> 01:03:53,931
But there'll be an empty room
when Min Seo goes to the US.

1011
01:03:53,991 --> 01:03:55,161
Absolutely not.

1012
01:03:56,531 --> 01:03:59,631
I promise you,
I will make Taehan yours.

1013
01:03:59,701 --> 01:04:02,601
I wonder if Taehan will
actually fall into my hands.

1014
01:04:03,841 --> 01:04:06,971
There's a term for people who are
possessive of a man who's no catch.

1015
01:04:06,971 --> 01:04:07,971
"Squid keeper."

1016
01:04:08,171 --> 01:04:10,511
If I ever see her around here,
she's going to get it.

1017
01:04:10,581 --> 01:04:15,351
She supposedly has a tailor shop
and lives alone with her brother.

1018
01:04:15,411 --> 01:04:19,121
- What's her name?
- It's Mi Hyang. Jo Mi Hyang.

1019
01:04:19,972 --> 01:04:21,972
Dramaday.me
